  "title": "La Dernière Nuit de la Reine / The Queen's Last Night",
  "description": "Galerie CAVA / 45 to 60 min / French and English performances / When all your deranged, sometimes humorous, sometimes tragic attempts at validation fail, what are you left with? Yourself? Oh, God, no! / “Raw, well-written and polished. Presents a reality not often heard of but all too familiar.” RAD – Showcase 2025.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Gilbert Drapeau<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Olivier Laroche<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Gilbert Drapeau<br/>",
  "website": "",
  "plain_language": "La Dernière Nuit de la Reine / The Queen’s Last Night tells the story of an older performer who is tired of living by other people’s rules. Looking back at his life, he sees how his family, community, and society's expectations shaped him. He learns from these sometimes humorous, sometimes tragic experiences and finds a way to free himself... or does he?",
